cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.FL, cs.DS 

The paper deals with type systems for probabilistic higher-order programs, which involves concepts from logic (such as reducibility) and programming languages (such as types). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with type systems and programming languages, which makes cs.PL (Programming Languages) another likely category. The paper also deals with termination, which is a topic in cs.TL (Theoretical Computer Science) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper deals with probabilistic programs, which involves probability theory and statistics, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category as well.
